Program: Outlook
Title: Pulling a Tooth at Gunpoint
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csvqq6
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 30 Nov 2017
Martha Ruiz-Perilla was studying to be a dentist when she was forced to operate on a teenage rebel in Colombia. Sven Marquardt is a doorman at the world-renowned Berlin nightclub, Berghain. He's responsible for deciding who gets in and who doesn't. Peter Turner was a young actor from Liverpool when he fell in love with a fading Hollywood movie star called Gloria Grahame. The movie 'Film Stars Don't Die in Liverpool' has just been made about their relationship. Miss Tic is a feminist graffiti art icon from France who insists on remaining anonymous. Image: dental equipment Credit: Coprid/Getty Images Show less